 The World Trade Organisation director-general Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala celebrates her sister Njideka Okonjo-Udochi for wining “Family Doctor Of The Year” in the US.  Njideka Okonjo-Udochi, was named Maryland’s family physician of the year, and her sister Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala took to Twitter to congratulate her sister. She wrote: Congratulations Dr Njideka Udochi, Maryland’s Family Physician Of The Year. Thank you for your care of COVID-19 patients and for saving so many lives. Proud of you my sister.” Congratulations Dr Njideka Udochi, Maryland’s Family Physician Of The Year. Thank you for your care of COVID-19 patients and for saving so many lives. Proud of you my sister. — Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala (@NOIweala) February 27, 2021 Okonjo-Udochi who graduated from The George Washington University School of Medicine and Health Sciences is described on her Linkedin page as an experienced medical director with a demonstrated history of working in the medical practice industry.